President Obama strongly condemns the attack on a British service member in Woolwich, London on May 22, 2013. The United States stands in solidarity with the United Kingdom against violent extremism and terrorism. The President expresses his condolences to the victim's family, as well as the police, security services, and British people affected by this horrific act. He emphasizes the importance of the special relationship between the United States and the United Kingdom during challenging times, and looks forward to participating in the June G-8 Summit hosted by Prime Minister Cameron, where global security challenges will be discussed.